# MarketDesk for AI Agents — API key configuration
#
# Copy this file to `.env` and edit:
#     cp .env.example .env
#
# Every wrapper script (scripts/*.py)
# loads it through scripts/_env.py at startup and maps values onto OpenBB
# credentials. `.env` is already in `.gitignore` (never commit it).
#
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Scope of this tool
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# MarketDesk is restricted to **ticker-level data**: quotes, fundamentals,
# financials, news, earnings calendars, SEC filings, and related feeds.
#
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# ============================================================================
# Optional: FMP (Financial Modeling Prep)
# ============================================================================
# Use: US equity fundamentals / three-statement financials / screener /
#      earnings calendar / institutional holdings.
#   - Free plan: 250 calls/day, US EOD only, 5y history, not for commercial use
#   - Starter ~$22/mo: 300/min, 5y history, commercial OK
#   - Premium $99/mo: 750/min, 30y history, UK/CA, intraday, corporate calendar
# Get a key: https://site.financialmodelingprep.com/developer/docs
#
# Most use cases are covered by Yahoo Finance even without this key. When set,
# OpenBB calls with `provider='fmp'` become available.
FMP_API_KEY=

# ============================================================================
# Required (when using SEC EDGAR): User-Agent
# ============================================================================
# SEC's official policy requires a User-Agent header for EDGAR API access.
# Format: "Name Email" (e.g., "AI Investment Research foo@example.com").
# Without it, SEC provider calls fail with 403.
SEC_USER_AGENT=

# ============================================================================
# Optional: FRED (for `obb.economy.survey.*`)
# ============================================================================
# Use: SLOOS / NY & Texas Fed manufacturing surveys / Michigan consumer
#      sentiment / inflation expectations / Chicago Fed activity index /
#      nonfarm payrolls, etc.
#   - OpenBB's survey wrappers are structured series with FRED as the primary
#     source. fred-api-ts cannot reproduce the same structured output easily,
#     so we fetch them through this tool.
#   - Free: issued immediately on signup, 120 req/min.
# Get a key: https://fred.stlouisfed.org/docs/api/api_key.html
#
FRED_API_KEY=

# ============================================================================
# Optional: EIA (U.S. Energy Information Administration)
# ============================================================================
# Use: short-term energy outlook (`obb.commodity.short_term_energy_outlook`,
#      i.e. `commodity.py --type steo`) via OpenBB's commodity namespace.
#      The STEO endpoint hits the EIA v2 API and requires this key.
#   - Free: issued immediately on signup, 5,000 req/day.
# Get a key: https://www.eia.gov/opendata/register.php
#
# NOTE: `commodity.py --type weekly_report` (Weekly Petroleum Status Report)
#       does NOT need this key — OpenBB downloads the public Excel file
#       directly. Spot commodity prices (`--type price`) use the FRED
#       provider and reuse FRED_API_KEY above. This key is only required
#       for `--type steo`.
EIA_API_KEY=

# ============================================================================
# Adding more providers
# ============================================================================
# OpenBB also bundles Polygon / Tiingo / Benzinga / Finnhub / Alpha Vantage,
# etc. When adding one, update both:
#   1. Add a variable here (e.g., POLYGON_API_KEY=...)
#   2. Add `{env var: credentials attribute}` to _CREDENTIAL_MAP in scripts/_env.py
# See README.md §6 "Extension Notes" for details.
